313  if (Perr) ERR_CRITICAL_FMT("Syntax:\n%s /P:ParamFile /O:OutputFile [/AP:AirTravelFile] [/s:SchoolFile] [/D:DensityFile] [/L:NetworkFileToLoad | /S:NetworkFileToSave] [/R:R0scaling] SetupSeed1 SetupSeed2 RunSeed1 RunSeed2\n", argv[0]);

319 #ifdef _OPENMP
320  P.NumThreads = omp_get_max_threads();
321  if ((P.MaxNumThreads > 0) && (P.MaxNumThreads < P.NumThreads)) P.NumThreads = P.MaxNumThreads;
322  if (P.NumThreads > MAX_NUM_THREADS)
323  {
324  fprintf(stderr, "Assigned number of threads (%d) > MAX_NUM_THREADS (%d)\n", P.NumThreads, MAX_NUM_THREADS);
325  P.NumThreads = MAX_NUM_THREADS;
326  }
327  fprintf(stderr, "Using %d threads\n", P.NumThreads);
328  omp_set_num_threads(P.NumThreads);
329 
330 #pragma omp parallel default(shared)
331  {
332  fprintf(stderr, "Thread %i initialised\n", omp_get_thread_num());
333  }
334  /* fprintf(stderr,"int=%i\tfloat=%i\tdouble=%i\tint *=%i\n",(int) sizeof(int),(int) sizeof(float),(int) sizeof(double),(int) sizeof(int *)); */
335 #else
336  P.NumThreads = 1;
337 #endif

347 
348  ReadParams(ParamFile, PreParamFile);
349  if (GotScF) P.DoSchoolFile = 1;
350  if (P.DoAirports)
351  {
352  if (!GotAP) ERR_CRITICAL_FMT("Syntax:\n%s /P:ParamFile /O:OutputFile /AP:AirTravelFile [/s:SchoolFile] [/D:DensityFile] [/L:NetworkFileToLoad | /S:NetworkFileToSave] [/R:R0scaling] SetupSeed1 SetupSeed2 RunSeed1 RunSeed2\n", argv[0]);
353  ReadAirTravel(AirTravelFile);
354  }
355 
359 
361  SetupModel(DensityFile, NetworkFile, SchoolFile, RegDemogFile);
362 
363  for (i = 0; i < MAX_ADUNITS; i++) AdUnits[i].NI = 0;
364  if (P.DoInterventionFile > 0)
365  for (i = 0; i < P.DoInterventionFile; i++)
366  ReadInterventions(InterventionFile[i]);
367 
368  fprintf(stderr, "Model setup in %lf seconds\n", ((double)(clock() - cl)) / CLOCKS_PER_SEC);
369 
370  //print out number of calls to random number generator
371 
375 
376 
377  P.NRactE = P.NRactNE = 0;
378  for (i = 0; (i < P.NumRealisations) && (P.NRactNE < P.NumNonExtinctRealisations) && (!InterruptRun); i++)
379  {
380  if (P.NumRealisations > 1)
381  {
382  sprintf(OutFile, "%s.%i", OutFileBase, i);
383  fprintf(stderr, "Realisation %i (time=%lf nr_ne=%i)\n", i + 1, ((double)(clock() - cl)) / CLOCKS_PER_SEC, P.NRactNE);
384  }
385 
387  if (i == 0 || (P.ResetSeeds && P.KeepSameSeeds))
388  {
389  P.nextRunSeed1 = P.runSeed1;
390  P.nextRunSeed2 = P.runSeed2;
391  }
392  if (P.ResetSeeds) {
393  //save these seeds to file
394  SaveRandomSeeds();
395  }
396  // Now that we have set P.nextRunSeed* ready for the run, we need to save the values in case
397  // we need to reinitialise the RNG after the run is interrupted.
398  long thisRunSeed1 = P.nextRunSeed1;
399  long thisRunSeed2 = P.nextRunSeed2;
400  if (i == 0 || P.ResetSeeds) {
401  setall(&P.nextRunSeed1, &P.nextRunSeed2);
402  //fprintf(stderr, "%i, %i\n", P.newseed1,P.newseed2);
403  //fprintf(stderr, "%f\n", ranf());
404  }
405 
407  InitModel(i); //passing run number into RunModel so we can save run number in the infection event log: ggilani - 15/10/2014
408  if (P.DoLoadSnapshot) LoadSnapshot();
409  while (RunModel(i))
410  { // has been interrupted to reset holiday time. Note that this currently only happens in the first run, regardless of how many realisations are being run.
411  long tmp1 = thisRunSeed1;
412  long tmp2 = thisRunSeed2;
413  setall(&tmp1, &tmp2); // reset random number seeds to generate same run again after calibration.
414  InitModel(i);
415  }
416  if (P.OutputNonSummaryResults)
417  {
418  if (((!TimeSeries[P.NumSamples - 1].extinct) || (!P.OutputOnlyNonExtinct)) && (P.OutputEveryRealisation))
419  {
420  SaveResults();
421  }
422  }
423  if ((P.DoRecordInfEvents) && (P.RecordInfEventsPerRun == 1))
424  {
425  SaveEvents();
426  }
427  }
428  sprintf(OutFile, "%s", OutFileBase);
429 
430  //Calculate origin destination matrix if needed
431  if ((P.DoAdUnits) && (P.DoOriginDestinationMatrix))
432  {
433  CalcOriginDestMatrix_adunit();
434  SaveOriginDestMatrix();
435  }
436 
437  P.NRactual = P.NRactNE;
438  TSMean = TSMeanNE; TSVar = TSVarNE;
439  if ((P.DoRecordInfEvents) && (P.RecordInfEventsPerRun == 0))
440  {
441  SaveEvents();
442  }
443  sprintf(OutFile, "%s.avNE", OutFileBase);
444  SaveSummaryResults();
445  P.NRactual = P.NRactE;
446  TSMean = TSMeanE; TSVar = TSVarE;
447  sprintf(OutFile, "%s.avE", OutFileBase);
448  //SaveSummaryResults();
449 
450  Bitmap_Finalise();
451 
452  fprintf(stderr, "Extinction in %i out of %i runs\n", P.NRactE, P.NRactNE + P.NRactE);
453  fprintf(stderr, "Model ran in %lf seconds\n", ((double)(clock() - cl)) / CLOCKS_PER_SEC);
454  fprintf(stderr, "Model finished\n");
455 }

458 void ReadParams(char* ParamFile, char* PreParamFile)
459 {
460  FILE* ParamFile_dat, * PreParamFile_dat, *AdminFile_dat;
461  double s, t, AgeSuscScale;
462  int i, j, k, f, nc, na;
463  char CountryNameBuf[128 * MAX_COUNTRIES], AdunitListNamesBuf[128 * MAX_ADUNITS];
464 
465  char* CountryNames[MAX_COUNTRIES];
466  for (i = 0; i < MAX_COUNTRIES; i++) { CountryNames[i] = CountryNameBuf + 128 * i; CountryNames[i][0] = 0; }
467  char* AdunitListNames[MAX_ADUNITS];
468  for (i = 0; i < MAX_ADUNITS; i++) { AdunitListNames[i] = AdunitListNamesBuf + 128 * i; AdunitListNames[i][0] = 0; }
469  if (!(ParamFile_dat = fopen(ParamFile, "rb"))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to open parameter file\n");
470  PreParamFile_dat = fopen(PreParamFile, "rb");
471  if (!(AdminFile_dat = fopen(AdunitFile, "rb"))) AdminFile_dat = ParamFile_dat;
472  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Longitude cut line", "%lf", (void*) & (P.LongitudeCutLine), 1, 1, 0)) {
473  P.LongitudeCutLine = -360.0;
474  }
475  AgeSuscScale = 1.0;
476  GetInputParameter(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Update timestep", "%lf", (void*) & (P.TimeStep), 1, 1, 0);
477  GetInputParameter(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Sampling timestep", "%lf", (void*) & (P.SampleStep), 1, 1, 0);
478  if (P.TimeStep > P.SampleStep) ERR_CRITICAL("Update step must be smaller than sampling step\n");
479  t = ceil(P.SampleStep / P.TimeStep - 1e-6);
480  P.UpdatesPerSample = (int)t;
481  P.TimeStep = P.SampleStep / t;
482  P.TimeStepsPerDay = ceil(1.0 / P.TimeStep - 1e-6);
483  fprintf(stderr, "Update step = %lf\nSampling step = %lf\nUpdates per sample=%i\nTimeStepsPerDay=%lf\n", P.TimeStep, P.SampleStep, P.UpdatesPerSample, P.TimeStepsPerDay);
484  GetInputParameter(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Sampling time", "%lf", (void*) & (P.SampleTime), 1, 1, 0);
485  P.NumSamples = 1 + (int)ceil(P.SampleTime / P.SampleStep);
486  GetInputParameter(ParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Population size", "%i", (void*) & (P.PopSize), 1, 1, 0);
487  GetInputParameter(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Number of realisations", "%i", (void*) & (P.NumRealisations), 1, 1, 0);
488  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Number of non-extinct realisations", "%i", (void*) & (P.NumNonExtinctRealisations), 1, 1, 0)) P.NumNonExtinctRealisations = P.NumRealisations;
489  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Maximum number of cases defining small outbreak", "%i", (void*) & (P.SmallEpidemicCases), 1, 1, 0)) P.SmallEpidemicCases = -1;
490  P.NC = -1;
491  GetInputParameter(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Number of micro-cells per spatial cell width", "%i", (void*) & (P.NMCL), 1, 1, 0);
492  //added parameter to reset seeds after every run
493  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Reset seeds for every run", "%i", (void*) & (P.ResetSeeds), 1, 1, 0)) P.ResetSeeds = 0;
494  if (P.ResetSeeds)
495  {
496  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Keep same seeds for every run", "%i", (void*) & (P.KeepSameSeeds), 1, 1, 0)) P.KeepSameSeeds = 0; //added this to control which seeds are used: ggilani 27/11/19
497  }
498  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Reset seeds after intervention", "%i", (void*) & (P.ResetSeedsPostIntervention), 1, 1, 0)) P.ResetSeedsPostIntervention = 0;
499  if (P.ResetSeedsPostIntervention)
500  {
501  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Time to reset seeds after intervention", "%i", (void*) & (P.TimeToResetSeeds), 1, 1, 0)) P.TimeToResetSeeds = 1000000;
502  }
503  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Include households", "%i", (void*) & (P.DoHouseholds), 1, 1, 0)) P.DoHouseholds = 1;

505  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "OutputAge" , "%i", (void*) & (P.OutputAge) , 1, 1, 0)) P.OutputAge = 1;
506  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "OutputSeverityAdminUnit" , "%i", (void*) & (P.OutputSeverityAdminUnit) , 1, 1, 0)) P.OutputSeverityAdminUnit = 1;
507  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "OutputSeverityAge" , "%i", (void*) & (P.OutputSeverityAge) , 1, 1, 0)) P.OutputSeverityAge = 1;
508  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "OutputR0" , "%i", (void*) & (P.OutputR0) , 1, 1, 0)) P.OutputR0 = 0;

511  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "OutputAdUnitVar" , "%i", (void*) & (P.OutputAdUnitVar) , 1, 1, 0)) P.OutputAdUnitVar = 0;
512  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "OutputHousehold" , "%i", (void*) & (P.OutputHousehold) , 1, 1, 0)) P.OutputHousehold = 0;
513  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "OutputInfType" , "%i", (void*) & (P.OutputInfType) , 1, 1, 0)) P.OutputInfType = 0;
514  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "OutputNonSeverity" , "%i", (void*) & (P.OutputNonSeverity) , 1, 1, 0)) P.OutputNonSeverity = 0;
515  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "OutputNonSummaryResults" , "%i", (void*) & (P.OutputNonSummaryResults) , 1, 1, 0)) P.OutputNonSummaryResults = 0;

517  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Kernel resolution", "%i", (void*)&P.NKR, 1, 1, 0)) P.NKR = 4000000;
518  if (P.NKR < 2000000)
519  {
520  ERR_CRITICAL_FMT("[Kernel resolution] needs to be at least 2000000 - not %d", P.NKR);
521  }
522  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Kernel higher resolution factor", "%i", (void*)&P.NK_HR, 1, 1, 0)) P.NK_HR = P.NKR / 1600;
523  if (P.NK_HR < 1 || P.NK_HR >= P.NKR)
524  {
525  ERR_CRITICAL_FMT("[Kernel higher resolution factor] needs to be in range [1, P.NKR = %d) - not %d", P.NKR, P.NK_HR);
526  }
527 
528  if (P.DoHouseholds)
529  {
530  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Household size distribution", "%lf", (void*)P.HouseholdSizeDistrib[0], MAX_HOUSEHOLD_SIZE, 1, 0);
531  GetInputParameter(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Household attack rate", "%lf", (void*) & (P.HouseholdTrans), 1, 1, 0);
532  GetInputParameter(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Household transmission denominator power", "%lf", (void*) & (P.HouseholdTransPow), 1, 1, 0);
533  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Correct age distribution after household allocation to exactly match specified demography", "%i", (void*)&(P.DoCorrectAgeDist), 1, 1, 0)) P.DoCorrectAgeDist = 0;
534  }
535  else
536  {
537  P.HouseholdTrans = 0.0;
538  P.HouseholdTransPow = 1.0;
539  P.HouseholdSizeDistrib[0][0] = 1.0;
540  for (i = 1; i < MAX_HOUSEHOLD_SIZE; i++)
541  P.HouseholdSizeDistrib[0][i] = 0;
542  }
543  for (i = 1; i < MAX_HOUSEHOLD_SIZE; i++)
544  P.HouseholdSizeDistrib[0][i] = P.HouseholdSizeDistrib[0][i] + P.HouseholdSizeDistrib[0][i - 1];
545  for (i = 0; i < MAX_HOUSEHOLD_SIZE; i++)
546  P.HouseholdDenomLookup[i] = 1 / pow(((double)(i + 1)), P.HouseholdTransPow);
547  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Include administrative units within countries", "%i", (void*) & (P.DoAdUnits), 1, 1, 0)) P.DoAdUnits = 1;
548  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Divisor for countries", "%i", (void*) & (P.CountryDivisor), 1, 1, 0)) P.CountryDivisor = 1;
549  if (P.DoAdUnits)
550  {
551  char** AdunitNames, * AdunitNamesBuf;
552  if (!(AdunitNames = (char**)malloc(3 * ADUNIT_LOOKUP_SIZE * sizeof(char*)))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to allocate temp storage\n");
553  if (!(AdunitNamesBuf = (char*)malloc(3 * ADUNIT_LOOKUP_SIZE * 360 * sizeof(char)))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to allocate temp storage\n");
554 
555  for (i = 0; i < ADUNIT_LOOKUP_SIZE; i++)
556  {
557  P.AdunitLevel1Lookup[i] = -1;
558  AdunitNames[3 * i] = AdunitNamesBuf + 3 * i * 360;
559  AdunitNames[3 * i + 1] = AdunitNamesBuf + 3 * i * 360 + 60;
560  AdunitNames[3 * i + 2] = AdunitNamesBuf + 3 * i * 360 + 160;
561  }
562  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Divisor for level 1 administrative units", "%i", (void*)&(P.AdunitLevel1Divisor), 1, 1, 0)) P.AdunitLevel1Divisor = 1;
563  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Mask for level 1 administrative units", "%i", (void*)&(P.AdunitLevel1Mask), 1, 1, 0)) P.AdunitLevel1Mask = 1000000000;
564  na = (GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Codes and country/province names for admin units", "%s", (void*)AdunitNames, 3 * ADUNIT_LOOKUP_SIZE, 1, 0)) / 3;
565  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Number of countries to include", "%i", (void*)&nc, 1, 1, 0)) nc = 0;
566  if ((na > 0) && (nc>0))
567  {
568  P.DoAdunitBoundaries = (nc > 0);
569  nc = abs(nc);
570  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "List of names of countries to include", "%s", (nc > 1) ? ((void*)CountryNames) : ((void*)CountryNames[0]), nc, 1, 0);
571  P.NumAdunits = 0;
572  for (i = 0; i < na; i++)
573  for (j = 0; j < nc; j++)
574  if ((AdunitNames[3 * i + 1][0]) && (!strcmp(AdunitNames[3 * i + 1], CountryNames[j])) && (atoi(AdunitNames[3 * i]) != 0))
575  {
576  AdUnits[P.NumAdunits].id = atoi(AdunitNames[3 * i]);
577  P.AdunitLevel1Lookup[(AdUnits[P.NumAdunits].id % P.AdunitLevel1Mask) / P.AdunitLevel1Divisor] = P.NumAdunits;
578  if (strlen(AdunitNames[3 * i + 1]) < 100) strcpy(AdUnits[P.NumAdunits].cnt_name, AdunitNames[3 * i + 1]);
579  if (strlen(AdunitNames[3 * i + 2]) < 200) strcpy(AdUnits[P.NumAdunits].ad_name, AdunitNames[3 * i + 2]);
580  // fprintf(stderr,"%i %s %s ## ",AdUnits[P.NumAdunits].id,AdUnits[P.NumAdunits].cnt_name,AdUnits[P.NumAdunits].ad_name);
581  P.NumAdunits++;
582  }
583  }
584  else
585  {
586  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Number of level 1 administrative units to include", "%i", (void*) & (P.NumAdunits), 1, 1, 0)) P.NumAdunits = 0;
587  if (P.NumAdunits > 0)
588  {
589  P.DoAdunitBoundaries = 1;
590  if (P.NumAdunits > MAX_ADUNITS) ERR_CRITICAL("MAX_ADUNITS too small.\n");
591  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "List of level 1 administrative units to include", "%s", (P.NumAdunits > 1) ? ((void*)AdunitListNames) : ((void*)AdunitListNames[0]), P.NumAdunits, 1, 0);
592  na = P.NumAdunits;
593  for (i = 0; i < P.NumAdunits; i++)
594  {
595  f = 0;
596  if (na > 0)
597  {
598  for (j = 0; (j < na) && (!f); j++) f = (!strcmp(AdunitNames[3 * j + 2], AdunitListNames[i]));
599  if(f) k = atoi(AdunitNames[3 * (j-1)]);
600  }
601  if ((na == 0) || (!f)) k = atoi(AdunitListNames[i]);
602  AdUnits[i].id = k;
603  P.AdunitLevel1Lookup[(k % P.AdunitLevel1Mask) / P.AdunitLevel1Divisor] = i;
604  for (j = 0; j < na; j++)
605  if (atoi(AdunitNames[3 * j]) == k)
606  {
607  if (strlen(AdunitNames[3 * j + 1]) < 100) strcpy(AdUnits[i].cnt_name, AdunitNames[3 * j + 1]);
608  if (strlen(AdunitNames[3 * j + 2]) < 200) strcpy(AdUnits[i].ad_name, AdunitNames[3 * j + 2]);
609  j = na;
610  }
611  }
612  }
613  else
614  P.DoAdunitBoundaries = 0;
615  }
616  free(AdunitNames);
617  free(AdunitNamesBuf);
618 
619  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Output incidence by administrative unit", "%i", (void*) & (P.DoAdunitOutput), 1, 1, 0)) P.DoAdunitOutput = 0;
620  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Draw administrative unit boundaries on maps", "%i", (void*) & (P.DoAdunitBoundaryOutput), 1, 1, 0)) P.DoAdunitBoundaryOutput = 0;
621  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Correct administrative unit populations", "%i", (void*) & (P.DoCorrectAdunitPop), 1, 1, 0)) P.DoCorrectAdunitPop = 0;
622  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Fix population size at specified value", "%i", (void*) & (P.DoSpecifyPop), 1, 1, 0)) P.DoSpecifyPop = 0;
623  fprintf(stderr, "Using %i administrative units\n", P.NumAdunits);
624  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Divisor for administrative unit codes for boundary plotting on bitmaps", "%i", (void*) & (P.AdunitBitmapDivisor), 1, 1, 0)) P.AdunitBitmapDivisor = 1;
625  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Only output household to place distance distribution for one administrative unit", "%i", (void*) & (P.DoOutputPlaceDistForOneAdunit), 1, 1, 0)) P.DoOutputPlaceDistForOneAdunit = 0;
626  if (P.DoOutputPlaceDistForOneAdunit)
627  {
628  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Administrative unit for which household to place distance distribution to be output", "%i", (void*) & (P.OutputPlaceDistAdunit), 1, 1, 0)) P.DoOutputPlaceDistForOneAdunit = 0;
629  }
630  }
631  else
632  {
633  P.DoAdunitBoundaries = P.DoAdunitBoundaryOutput = P.DoAdunitOutput = P.DoCorrectAdunitPop = P.DoSpecifyPop = 0;
634  P.AdunitLevel1Divisor = 1; P.AdunitLevel1Mask = 1000000000;
635  P.AdunitBitmapDivisor = P.AdunitLevel1Divisor;
636  }
637 
638  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Include age", "%i", (void*) & (P.DoAge), 1, 1, 0)) P.DoAge = 1;
639  if (!P.DoAge)
640  {
641  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++)
642  P.PropAgeGroup[0][i] = 1.0 / NUM_AGE_GROUPS;
643  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++)
644  {
645  P.InitialImmunity[i] = 0;
646  P.AgeInfectiousness[i] = P.AgeSusceptibility[i] = 1;
647  P.RelativeSpatialContact[i] = P.RelativeTravelRate[i] = 1.0;
648  }
649  }
650  else
651  {
652 
653  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Initial immunity acts as partial immunity", "%i", (void*)&(P.DoPartialImmunity), 1, 1, 0)) P.DoPartialImmunity = 1;
654  if ((P.DoHouseholds)&&(!P.DoPartialImmunity))
655  {
656  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Initial immunity applied to all household members", "%i", (void*) & (P.DoWholeHouseholdImmunity), 1, 1, 0)) P.DoWholeHouseholdImmunity = 0;
657  }
658  else
659  P.DoWholeHouseholdImmunity = 0;
660  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Initial immunity profile by age", "%lf", (void*)P.InitialImmunity, NUM_AGE_GROUPS, 1, 0))
661  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++)
662  P.InitialImmunity[i] = 0;
663  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Relative spatial contact rates by age", "%lf", (void*)P.RelativeSpatialContact, NUM_AGE_GROUPS, 1, 0))
664  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++)
665  P.RelativeSpatialContact[i] = 1;
666  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Age-dependent infectiousness", "%lf", (void*)P.AgeInfectiousness, NUM_AGE_GROUPS, 1, 0))
667  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++)
668  P.AgeInfectiousness[i] = 1.0;
669  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Age-dependent susceptibility", "%lf", (void*)P.AgeSusceptibility, NUM_AGE_GROUPS, 1, 0))
670  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++)
671  P.AgeSusceptibility[i] = 1.0;
672  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Age distribution of population", "%lf", (void*)P.PropAgeGroup[0], NUM_AGE_GROUPS, 1, 0);
673  t = 0;
674  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++)
675  t += P.PropAgeGroup[0][i];
676  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++)
677  P.PropAgeGroup[0][i] /= t;
678  t = 0;
679  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++)
680  if (P.AgeSusceptibility[i] > t) t = P.AgeSusceptibility[i]; //peak susc has to be 1
681  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++)
682  P.AgeSusceptibility[i] /= t;
683  AgeSuscScale = t;
684  if (P.DoHouseholds) P.HouseholdTrans *= AgeSuscScale;
685  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Relative travel rates by age", "%lf", (void*)P.RelativeTravelRate, NUM_AGE_GROUPS, 1, 0))
686  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++)
687  P.RelativeTravelRate[i] = 1;
688  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "WAIFW matrix", "%lf", (void*)P.WAIFW_Matrix, NUM_AGE_GROUPS, NUM_AGE_GROUPS, 0))
689  {
690  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++)
691  for (j = 0; j < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; j++)
692  P.WAIFW_Matrix[i][j] = 1.0;
693  }
694  else
695  {
696  /* WAIFW matrix needs to be scaled to have max value of 1.
697  1st index of matrix specifies host being infected, second the infector.
698  Overall age variation in infectiousness/contact rates/susceptibility should be factored
699  out of WAIFW_matrix and put in Age dep infectiousness/susceptibility for efficiency. */
700  t = 0;
701  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++)
702  for (j = 0; j < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; j++)
703  if (P.WAIFW_Matrix[i][j] > t) t = P.WAIFW_Matrix[i][j];
704  if (t > 0)
705  {
706  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++)
707  for (j = 0; j < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; j++)
708  P.WAIFW_Matrix[i][j] /= t;
709  }
710  else
711  {
712  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++)
713  for (j = 0; j < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; j++)
714  P.WAIFW_Matrix[i][j] = 1.0;
715  }
716  }
717  P.DoDeath = 0;
718  t = 0;
719  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++) t += P.AgeInfectiousness[i] * P.PropAgeGroup[0][i];
720  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++) P.AgeInfectiousness[i] /= t;
721  }
722  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Include spatial transmission", "%i", (void*) & (P.DoSpatial), 1, 1, 0)) P.DoSpatial = 1;
723  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Kernel type", "%i", (void*) & (P.MoveKernelType), 1, 1, 0);
724  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Kernel scale", "%lf", (void*) & (P.MoveKernelScale), 1, 1, 0);
725  if (P.KernelOffsetScale != 1)
726  {
727  P.MoveKernelScale *= P.KernelOffsetScale;
728  }
729  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Kernel 3rd param", "%lf", (void*) & (P.MoveKernelP3), 1, 1, 0)) P.MoveKernelP3 = 0;
730  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Kernel 4th param", "%lf", (void*) & (P.MoveKernelP4), 1, 1, 0)) P.MoveKernelP4 = 0;
731  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Kernel Shape", "%lf", (void*) & (P.MoveKernelShape), 1, 1, 0)) P.MoveKernelShape = 1.0;
732  if (P.KernelPowerScale != 1)
733  {
734  P.MoveKernelShape *= P.KernelPowerScale;
735  }
736  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Airport Kernel Type", "%i", (void*) & (P.AirportKernelType), 1, 1, 0)) P.AirportKernelType = P.MoveKernelType;
737  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Airport Kernel Scale", "%lf", (void*) & (P.AirportKernelScale), 1, 1, 0)) P.AirportKernelScale = P.MoveKernelScale;
738  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Airport Kernel Shape", "%lf", (void*) & (P.AirportKernelShape), 1, 1, 0)) P.AirportKernelShape = P.MoveKernelShape;
739  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Airport Kernel 3rd param", "%lf", (void*) & (P.AirportKernelP3), 1, 1, 0)) P.AirportKernelP3 = P.MoveKernelP3;
740  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Airport Kernel 4th param", "%lf", (void*) & (P.AirportKernelP4), 1, 1, 0)) P.AirportKernelP4 = P.MoveKernelP4;
741 
742  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Include places", "%i", (void*)&(P.DoPlaces), 1, 1, 0)) P.DoPlaces = 1;
743  if (P.DoPlaces)
744  {
745  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Number of types of places", "%i", (void*)&(P.PlaceTypeNum), 1, 1, 0)) P.PlaceTypeNum = 0;
746  if (P.PlaceTypeNum == 0) P.DoPlaces = P.DoAirports = 0;
747  }
748  else
749  P.PlaceTypeNum = P.DoAirports = 0;
750  if (P.DoPlaces)
751  {
752  if (P.PlaceTypeNum > NUM_PLACE_TYPES) ERR_CRITICAL("Too many place types\n");
753  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Minimum age for age group 1 in place types", "%i", (void*)P.PlaceTypeAgeMin, P.PlaceTypeNum, 1, 0);
754  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Maximum age for age group 1 in place types", "%i", (void*)P.PlaceTypeAgeMax, P.PlaceTypeNum, 1, 0);
755  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Proportion of age group 1 in place types", "%lf", (void*) & (P.PlaceTypePropAgeGroup), P.PlaceTypeNum, 1, 0);
756  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Proportion of age group 2 in place types", "%lf", (void*) & (P.PlaceTypePropAgeGroup2), P.PlaceTypeNum, 1, 0))
757  {
758  for (i = 0; i < NUM_PLACE_TYPES; i++)
759  {
760  P.PlaceTypePropAgeGroup2[i] = 0;
761  P.PlaceTypeAgeMin2[i] = 0;
762  P.PlaceTypeAgeMax2[i] = 1000;
763  }
764  }
765  else
766  {
767  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Minimum age for age group 2 in place types", "%i", (void*)P.PlaceTypeAgeMin2, P.PlaceTypeNum, 1, 0);
768  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Maximum age for age group 2 in place types", "%i", (void*)P.PlaceTypeAgeMax2, P.PlaceTypeNum, 1, 0);
769  }
770  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Proportion of age group 3 in place types", "%lf", (void*) & (P.PlaceTypePropAgeGroup3), P.PlaceTypeNum, 1, 0))
771  {
772  for (i = 0; i < NUM_PLACE_TYPES; i++)
773  {
774  P.PlaceTypePropAgeGroup3[i] = 0;
775  P.PlaceTypeAgeMin3[i] = 0;
776  P.PlaceTypeAgeMax3[i] = 1000;
777  }
778  }
779  else
780  {
781  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Minimum age for age group 3 in place types", "%i", (void*)P.PlaceTypeAgeMin3, P.PlaceTypeNum, 1, 0);
782  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Maximum age for age group 3 in place types", "%i", (void*)P.PlaceTypeAgeMax3, P.PlaceTypeNum, 1, 0);
783  }
784  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Kernel shape params for place types", "%lf", (void*) & (P.PlaceTypeKernelShape), P.PlaceTypeNum, 1, 0))
785  {
786  for (i = 0; i < NUM_PLACE_TYPES; i++)
787  {
788  P.PlaceTypeKernelShape[i] = P.MoveKernelShape;
789  P.PlaceTypeKernelScale[i] = P.MoveKernelScale;
790  }
791  }
792  else
793  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Kernel scale params for place types", "%lf", (void*) & (P.PlaceTypeKernelScale), P.PlaceTypeNum, 1, 0);
794  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Kernel 3rd param for place types", "%lf", (void*) & (P.PlaceTypeKernelP3), P.PlaceTypeNum, 1, 0))
795  {
796  for (i = 0; i < NUM_PLACE_TYPES; i++)
797  {
798  P.PlaceTypeKernelP3[i] = P.MoveKernelP3;
799  P.PlaceTypeKernelP4[i] = P.MoveKernelP4;
800  }
801  }
802  else
803  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Kernel 4th param for place types", "%lf", (void*) & (P.PlaceTypeKernelP4), P.PlaceTypeNum, 1, 0);
804  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Number of closest places people pick from (0=all) for place types", "%i", (void*) & (P.PlaceTypeNearestNeighb), P.PlaceTypeNum, 1, 0))
805  for (i = 0; i < NUM_PLACE_TYPES; i++)
806  P.PlaceTypeNearestNeighb[i] = 0;
807  if (P.DoAdUnits)
808  {
809  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Degree to which crossing administrative unit boundaries to go to places is inhibited", "%lf", (void*) & (P.InhibitInterAdunitPlaceAssignment), P.PlaceTypeNum, 1, 0))
810  for (i = 0; i < NUM_PLACE_TYPES; i++)
811  P.InhibitInterAdunitPlaceAssignment[i] = 0;

840  for (i = 0; i < MAX_TRAVEL_TIME; i++)
841  P.JourneyDurationDistrib[i] = 0;
842  }
843  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Distribution of duration of local journeys", "%lf", (void*) & (P.LocalJourneyDurationDistrib), MAX_TRAVEL_TIME, 1, 0))
844  {
845  P.LocalJourneyDurationDistrib[0] = 1;
846  for (i = 0; i < MAX_TRAVEL_TIME; i++)
847  P.LocalJourneyDurationDistrib[i] = 0;

849  P.MeanJourneyTime = P.MeanLocalJourneyTime = 0;
850  for (i = 0; i < MAX_TRAVEL_TIME; i++)
851  {

853  P.MeanLocalJourneyTime += ((double)(i)) * P.LocalJourneyDurationDistrib[i];
854  }
855  fprintf(stderr, "Mean duration of local journeys = %lf days\n", P.MeanLocalJourneyTime);
856  for (i = 1; i < MAX_TRAVEL_TIME; i++)
857  {

859  P.LocalJourneyDurationDistrib[i] += P.LocalJourneyDurationDistrib[i - 1];
860  }

862  {

864  while (P.JourneyDurationDistrib[j] < s)j++;
865  P.InvJourneyDurationDistrib[i] = j;
866  }

976  if (P.DoInfectiousnessProfile)
977  {
978  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Infectiousness profile", "%lf", (void*)P.infectious_prof, INFPROF_RES, 1, 0))
979  {
980  for (i = 0; i < INFPROF_RES; i++)
981  P.infectious_prof[i] = 1;
982  }
983  k = (int)ceil(P.InfectiousPeriod / P.TimeStep);
984  if (k >= MAX_INFECTIOUS_STEPS) ERR_CRITICAL("MAX_INFECTIOUS_STEPS not big enough\n");
985  s = 0;
986  P.infectious_prof[INFPROF_RES] = 0;
987  for (i = 0; i < MAX_INFECTIOUS_STEPS; i++) P.infectiousness[i] = 0;
988  for (i = 0; i < k; i++)
989  {
990  t = (((double)i) * P.TimeStep / P.InfectiousPeriod * INFPROF_RES);
991  j = (int)t;
992  t -= (double)j;
993  if (j < INFPROF_RES)
994  s += (P.infectiousness[i] = P.infectious_prof[j] * (1 - t) + P.infectious_prof[j + 1] * t);
995  else
996  s += (P.infectiousness[i] = P.infectious_prof[INFPROF_RES]);
997  }
998  s /= ((double)k);
999  for (i = 0; i <= k; i++) P.infectiousness[i] /= s;
1000  for (i = 0; i <= CDF_RES; i++) P.infectious_icdf[i] = exp(-1.0);
1001  }
1002  else
1003  {
1004  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Infectious period inverse CDF", "%lf", (void*)P.infectious_icdf, CDF_RES + 1, 1, 0))
1005  {
1006  P.infectious_icdf[CDF_RES] = 100;
1007  for (i = 0; i < CDF_RES; i++)
1008  P.infectious_icdf[i] = -log(1 - ((double)i) / CDF_RES);
1009  }
1010  k = (int)ceil(P.InfectiousPeriod * P.infectious_icdf[CDF_RES] / P.TimeStep);
1011  if (k >= MAX_INFECTIOUS_STEPS) ERR_CRITICAL("MAX_INFECTIOUS_STEPS not big enough\n");
1012  for (i = 0; i < k; i++) P.infectiousness[i] = 1.0;
1013  P.infectiousness[k] = 0;
1014  for (i = 0; i <= CDF_RES; i++) P.infectious_icdf[i] = exp(-P.infectious_icdf[i]);
1015  }

2081  {
2082  asin2sqx[i] = asin(sqrt(((double)(i)) / 1000));
2083  asin2sqx[i] = asin2sqx[i] * asin2sqx[i];
2084  }
2085  for (t = 0; t <= 360; t++)
2086  {
2087  sinx[(int)t] = sin(PI * t / 180);
2088  cosx[(int)t] = cos(PI * t / 180);
2089  }
2090  }
2091  fprintf(stderr, "Parameters read\n");
2092 }

2300 int GetXMLNode(FILE* dat, const char* NodeName, const char* ParentName, char* Value, int ResetFilePos)
2301 {
2302  // ResetFilePos=1 leaves dat cursor in same position as when function was called. 0 leaves it at end of NodeName closure
2303  // GetXMLNode returns 1 if NodeName found, 0 otherwise. If NodeName not found, ParentName closure must be
2304 
2305  char buf[65536], CloseNode[2048], CloseParent[2048];
2306  int CurPos, ret;
2307 
2308  sprintf(CloseParent, "/%s", ParentName);
2309  CurPos = ftell(dat);
2310  do
2311  {
2312  if(fscanf(dat, "%*[^<]<%[^>]", buf) != 1) {
2313  ERR_CRITICAL("fscanf failed in GetXMLNode");
2314  }
2315  } while ((strcmp(buf, CloseParent) != 0) && (strcmp(buf, NodeName) != 0) && (!feof(dat)));
2316  if (strcmp(buf, CloseParent) == 0)
2317  ret = 0;
2318  else
2319  {
2320  if (strcmp(buf, NodeName) != 0) ERR_CRITICAL("Incomplete node specification in XML file\n");
2321  if(fscanf(dat, ">%[^<]", buf) != 1) {
2322  ERR_CRITICAL("fscanf failed in GetXMLNode");
2323  }
2324  if (strlen(buf) < 2048) strcpy(Value, buf);
2325  // fprintf(stderr,"# %s=%s\n",NodeName,Value);
2326  if(fscanf(dat, "<%[^>]", buf) != 1) {
2327  ERR_CRITICAL("fscanf failed in GetXMLNode");
2328  }
2329  sprintf(CloseNode, "/%s", NodeName);
2330  if (strcmp(buf, CloseNode) != 0) ERR_CRITICAL("Incomplete node specification in XML file\n");
2331  ret = 1;
2332  }
2333  if (ResetFilePos) fseek(dat, CurPos, 0);
2334  return ret;
2335 }
2336 void ReadAirTravel(char* AirTravelFile)
2337 {
2338  int i, j, k, l;
2339  float sc, t, t2;
2340  float* buf;
2341  double traf;
2342  char outname[1024];
2343  FILE* dat;
2344 
2345  fprintf(stderr, "Reading airport data...\nAirports with no connections = ");
2346  if (!(dat = fopen(AirTravelFile, "rb"))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to open airport file\n");
2347  if(fscanf(dat, "%i %i", &P.Nairports, &P.Air_popscale) != 2) {
2348  ERR_CRITICAL("fscanf failed in void ReadAirTravel\n");
2349  }
2350  sc = (float)((double)P.PopSize / (double)P.Air_popscale);
2351  if (P.Nairports > MAX_AIRPORTS) ERR_CRITICAL("Too many airports\n");
2352  if (P.Nairports < 2) ERR_CRITICAL("Too few airports\n");
2353  if (!(buf = (float*)calloc(P.Nairports + 1, sizeof(float)))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to allocate airport storage\n");
2354  if (!(Airports = (Airport*)calloc(P.Nairports, sizeof(Airport)))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to allocate airport storage\n");
2355  for (i = 0; i < P.Nairports; i++)
2356  {
2357  if(fscanf(dat, "%f %f %lf", &(Airports[i].loc_x), &(Airports[i].loc_y), &traf) != 3) {
2358  ERR_CRITICAL("fscanf failed in void ReadAirTravel\n");
2359  }
2360  traf *= (P.AirportTrafficScale * sc);
2361  if ((Airports[i].loc_x < P.SpatialBoundingBox[0]) || (Airports[i].loc_x >= P.SpatialBoundingBox[2])
2362  || (Airports[i].loc_y < P.SpatialBoundingBox[1]) || (Airports[i].loc_y >= P.SpatialBoundingBox[3]))
2363  {
2364  Airports[i].loc_x = Airports[i].loc_y = -1;
2365  Airports[i].total_traffic = 0;
2366  }
2367  else
2368  {
2369  //fprintf(stderr,"(%f\t%f) ",Airports[i].loc_x,Airports[i].loc_y);
2370  Airports[i].loc_x -= (float)P.SpatialBoundingBox[0];
2371  Airports[i].loc_y -= (float)P.SpatialBoundingBox[1];
2372  Airports[i].total_traffic = (float)traf;
2373  }
2374  t = 0;
2375  for (j = k = 0; j < P.Nairports; j++)
2376  {
2377  if(fscanf(dat, "%f", buf + j) != 1) {
2378  ERR_CRITICAL("fscanf failed in void ReadAirTravel\n");
2379  }
2380  if (buf[j] > 0) { k++; t += buf[j]; }
2381  }
2382  Airports[i].num_connected = k;
2383  if (Airports[i].num_connected > 0)
2384  {
2385  if (!(Airports[i].prop_traffic = (float*)calloc(Airports[i].num_connected, sizeof(float)))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to allocate airport storage\n");
2386  if (!(Airports[i].conn_airports = (unsigned short int*) calloc(Airports[i].num_connected, sizeof(unsigned short int)))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to allocate airport storage\n");
2387  for (j = k = 0; j < P.Nairports; j++)
2388  if (buf[j] > 0)
2389  {
2390  Airports[i].conn_airports[k] = j;
2391  Airports[i].prop_traffic[k] = buf[j] / t;
2392  k++;
2393  }
2394  }
2395  else
2396  {
2397  if (Airports[i].total_traffic > 0)
2398  fprintf(stderr, "#%i# ", i);
2399  else
2400  fprintf(stderr, "%i ", i);
2401  }
2402  }
2403  fclose(dat);
2404  free(buf);
2405  fprintf(stderr, "\nAirport data read OK.\n");
2406  for (i = 0; i < P.Nairports; i++)
2407  {
2408  /* fprintf(stderr,"(%f %i|",Airports[i].total_traffic,Airports[i].num_connected);
2409  */ t = 0; k = 0;
2410  for (j = Airports[i].num_connected - 1; j >= 0; j--)
2411  {
2412  if ((Airports[i].prop_traffic[j] > 0) && (Airports[Airports[i].conn_airports[j]].total_traffic == 0))
2413  {
2414  t += Airports[i].prop_traffic[j];
2415  Airports[i].num_connected--;
2416  if (j < Airports[i].num_connected)
2417  {
2418  Airports[i].prop_traffic[j] = Airports[i].prop_traffic[Airports[i].num_connected];
2419  Airports[i].conn_airports[j] = Airports[i].conn_airports[Airports[i].num_connected];
2420  }
2421  Airports[i].prop_traffic[Airports[i].num_connected] = 0;
2422  Airports[i].conn_airports[Airports[i].num_connected] = 0;
2423  }
2424  else if (Airports[i].prop_traffic[j] > 0)
2425  k = 1;
2426  }
2427  /* fprintf(stderr,"%f %i ",t,k);
2428  */ t = 1.0f - t;
2429  if (k)
2430  {
2431  Airports[i].total_traffic *= t;
2432  t2 = 0;
2433  for (j = 0; j < Airports[i].num_connected; j++)
2434  {
2435  Airports[i].prop_traffic[j] = t2 + Airports[i].prop_traffic[j];
2436  t2 = Airports[i].prop_traffic[j];
2437  }
2438  for (j = 0; j < Airports[i].num_connected; j++)
2439  Airports[i].prop_traffic[j] /= t2;
2440  /* if((Airports[i].num_connected>0)&&(Airports[i].prop_traffic[Airports[i].num_connected-1]!=1))
2441  fprintf(stderr,"<%f> ",Airports[i].prop_traffic[Airports[i].num_connected-1]);
2442  */
2443  }
2444  else
2445  {
2446  Airports[i].total_traffic = 0; Airports[i].num_connected = 0;
2447  }
2448  if (Airports[i].num_connected > 0)
2449  {
2450  for (j = k = 0; k < 128; k++)
2451  {
2452  t = (float)((double)k / 128);
2453  while (Airports[i].prop_traffic[j] < t) j++;
2454  Airports[i].Inv_prop_traffic[k] = j;
2455  }
2456  Airports[i].Inv_prop_traffic[128] = Airports[i].num_connected - 1;
2457  }
2458  /* fprintf(stderr,"%f) ",Airports[i].total_traffic);
2459  */
2460  }
2461  fprintf(stderr, "Airport data clipped OK.\n");
2462  for (i = 0; i < MAX_DIST; i++) AirTravelDist[i] = 0;
2463  for (i = 0; i < P.Nairports; i++)
2464  if (Airports[i].total_traffic > 0)
2465  {
2466  for (j = 0; j < Airports[i].num_connected; j++)
2467  {
2468  k = (int)Airports[i].conn_airports[j];
2469  traf = floor(sqrt(dist2_raw(Airports[i].loc_x, Airports[i].loc_y, Airports[k].loc_x, Airports[k].loc_y)) / OUTPUT_DIST_SCALE);
2470  l = (int)traf;
2471  //fprintf(stderr,"%(%i) ",l);
2472  if (l < MAX_DIST)
2473  AirTravelDist[l] += Airports[i].total_traffic * Airports[i].prop_traffic[j];
2474  }
2475  }
2476  sprintf(outname, "%s.airdist.xls", OutFile);
2477  if (!(dat = fopen(outname, "wb"))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to open air travel output file\n");
2478  fprintf(dat, "dist\tfreq\n");
2479  for (i = 0; i < MAX_DIST; i++)
2480  fprintf(dat, "%i\t%.10f\n", i, AirTravelDist[i]);
2481  fclose(dat);
2482 }

2517  State.cumDeath_ILI = State.cumDeath_SARI = State.cumDeath_Critical = 0;
2518

2520  {

2830 
2831 void SeedInfection(double t, int* nsi, int rf, int run) //adding run number to pass it to event log
2832 {
2833  /* *nsi is an array of the number of seeding infections by location. During runtime, usually just a single int (given by a poisson distribution)*/
2834  /*rf set to 0 when initializing model, otherwise set to 1 during runtime. */
2835 
2836  int i /*seed location index*/;
2837  int j /*microcell number*/;
2838  int k, l /*k,l are grid coords at first, then l changed to be person within Microcell j, then k changed to be index of new infection*/;
2839  int m = 0/*guard against too many infections and infinite loop*/;
2840  int f /*range = {0, 1000}*/;
2841  int n /*number of seed locations?*/;
2842 
2843  n = ((rf == 0) ? P.NumSeedLocations : 1);
2844  for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
2845  {
2846  if ((!P.DoRandomInitialInfectionLoc) || ((P.DoAllInitialInfectioninSameLoc) && (rf)))
2847  {
2848  k = (int)(P.LocationInitialInfection[i][0] / P.mcwidth);
2849  l = (int)(P.LocationInitialInfection[i][1] / P.mcheight);
2850  j = k * P.nmch + l;
2851  m = 0;
2852  for (k = 0; (k < nsi[i]) && (m < 10000); k++)
2853  {
2854  l = Mcells[j].members[(int)(ranf() * ((double)Mcells[j].n))];
2855  if (Hosts[l].inf == InfStat_Susceptible)
2856  {
2857  if (CalcPersonSusc(l, 0, 0, 0) > 0)
2858  {
2859  //only reset the initial location if rf==0, i.e. when initial seeds are being set, not when imported cases are being set
2860  if (rf == 0)
2861  {
2862  P.LocationInitialInfection[i][0] = Households[Hosts[l].hh].loc_x;
2863  P.LocationInitialInfection[i][1] = Households[Hosts[l].hh].loc_y;
2864  }
2865  Hosts[l].infector = -2;
2866  Hosts[l].infect_type = INFECT_TYPE_MASK - 1;
2867  DoInfect(l, t, 0, run);
2868  m = 0;
2869  }
2870  }
2871  else { k--; m++; }
2872  }
2873  }
2874  else if (P.DoAllInitialInfectioninSameLoc)
2875  {
2876  f = 0;
2877  do
2878  {
2879  m = 0;
2880  do
2881  {
2882  l = (int)(ranf() * ((double)P.PopSize));
2883  j = Hosts[l].mcell;
2884  //fprintf(stderr,"%i ",AdUnits[Mcells[j].adunit].id);
2885  } while ((Mcells[j].n < nsi[i]) || (Mcells[j].n > P.MaxPopDensForInitialInfection)
2886  || (Mcells[j].n < P.MinPopDensForInitialInfection)
2887  || ((P.InitialInfectionsAdminUnit[i] > 0) && ((AdUnits[Mcells[j].adunit].id % P.AdunitLevel1Mask) / P.AdunitLevel1Divisor != (P.InitialInfectionsAdminUnit[i] % P.AdunitLevel1Mask) / P.AdunitLevel1Divisor)));
2888  for (k = 0; (k < nsi[i]) && (m < 10000); k++)
2889  {
2890  l = Mcells[j].members[(int)(ranf() * ((double)Mcells[j].n))];
2891  if (Hosts[l].inf == InfStat_Susceptible)
2892  {
2893  if (CalcPersonSusc(l, 0, 0, 0) > 0)
2894  {
2895  P.LocationInitialInfection[i][0] = Households[Hosts[l].hh].loc_x;
2896  P.LocationInitialInfection[i][1] = Households[Hosts[l].hh].loc_y;
2897  Hosts[l].infector = -2; Hosts[l].infect_type = INFECT_TYPE_MASK - 1;
2898  DoInfect(l, t, 0, run);
2899  m = 0;
2900  }
2901  }
2902  else
2903  {
2904  k--; m++;
2905  }
2906  }
2907  if (m)
2908  f++;
2909  else
2910  f = 0;
2911  } while ((f > 0) && (f < 1000));
2912  }
2913  else
2914  {
2915  m = 0;
2916  for (k = 0; (k < nsi[i]) && (m < 10000); k++)
2917  {
2918  do
2919  {
2920  l = (int)(ranf() * ((double)P.PopSize));
2921  j = Hosts[l].mcell;
2922  //fprintf(stderr,"@@ %i %i ",AdUnits[Mcells[j].adunit].id, (int)(AdUnits[Mcells[j].adunit].id / P.CountryDivisor));
2923  } while ((Mcells[j].n == 0) || (Mcells[j].n > P.MaxPopDensForInitialInfection)
2924  || (Mcells[j].n < P.MinPopDensForInitialInfection)
2925  || ((P.InitialInfectionsAdminUnit[i] > 0) && ((AdUnits[Mcells[j].adunit].id % P.AdunitLevel1Mask) / P.AdunitLevel1Divisor != (P.InitialInfectionsAdminUnit[i] % P.AdunitLevel1Mask) / P.AdunitLevel1Divisor)));
2926  l = Mcells[j].members[(int)(ranf() * ((double)Mcells[j].n))];
2927  if (Hosts[l].inf == InfStat_Susceptible)
2928  {
2929  if (CalcPersonSusc(l, 0, 0, 0) > 0)
2930  {
2931  P.LocationInitialInfection[i][0] = Households[Hosts[l].hh].loc_x;
2932  P.LocationInitialInfection[i][1] = Households[Hosts[l].hh].loc_y;
2933  Hosts[l].infector = -2; Hosts[l].infect_type = INFECT_TYPE_MASK - 1;
2934  DoInfect(l, t, 0, run);
2935  m = 0;
2936  }
2937  else
2938  {
2939  k--; m++;
2940  }
2941  }
2942  else
2943  {
2944  k--; m++;
2945  }
2946  }
2947  }
2948  }
2949  if (m > 0) fprintf(stderr, "### Seeding error ###\n");
2950 }

2954 {

2976  }

2981  }

2992  InterruptRun = 0;

3000  {

3005  fs2 = 0;
3006  nu = 0;

3009  {

3011  fprintf(stderr, "\r t=%lg %i %i|%i %i %i [=%i] %i (%lg %lg %lg) %lg ", t,

3013  if (!InterruptRun)
3014  {
3015  //Only run to a certain number of infections: ggilani 28/10/14
3016  if (P.LimitNumInfections) continueEvents = (State.cumI < P.MaxNumInfections);
3017 
3018  for (j = 0; ((j < P.UpdatesPerSample) && (!InterruptRun) && (continueEvents)); j++)
3019  {
3020  ts = (unsigned short int) (P.TimeStepsPerDay * t);
3021 
3022  //if we are to reset random numbers after an intervention event, specific time
3023  if (P.ResetSeedsPostIntervention)
3024  if ((P.ResetSeedsFlag == 0) && (ts >= (P.TimeToResetSeeds * P.TimeStepsPerDay)))

3034  if (P.DurImportTimeProfile > 0)
3035  {

3037  ir = P.ImportInfectionTimeProfile[k] * ((t > P.InfectionImportChangeTime) ? (P.InfectionImportRate2 / P.InfectionImportRate1) : 1.0);
3038  else
3039  ir = 0;
3040  }
3041  else ir = (t > P.InfectionImportChangeTime) ? P.InfectionImportRate2 : P.InfectionImportRate1;

3045  if (ni > 0) SeedInfection(t, nsi, 1, run);
3046  }

3048  {

3050  if (ni > 0)

3053  {
3054  do

3058  DoFalseCase(l, t, ts, 0);
3059  }
3060  }
3061  }
3062  InfectSweep(t, run); // loops over all infectious people and decides which susceptible people to infect (at household, place and spatial level), and adds them to queue. Then changes each person's various characteristics using DoInfect function. adding run number as a parameter to infect sweep so we can track run number: ggilani - 15/10/14

3068

3074  if ((!fs2) && (State.L + State.I == 0) && (P.FalsePositivePerCapitaIncidence == 0)) { if ((ir == 0) && (((int)t) > P.DurImportTimeProfile)) fs = 0; }
3075  }

3077  }

3088  DoInitUpdateProbs = 1;
3089  }
3090  }
3091  }
3092  }

3094  fprintf(stderr, "\nEnd of run\n");
3095  t2 = t + P.SampleTime;
3096 // if(!InterruptRun)
3097  while (fs)
3098  {
3099  fs = TreatSweep(t2);
3100  t2 += P.SampleStep;
3101  }
3102  // fprintf(stderr,"End RunModel\n");
3103  if (P.DoAirports)
3104  {
3105  t2 = t;
3106  for (t2 = t; t2 <= t + MAX_TRAVEL_TIME; t2 += P.TimeStep)
3107  TravelReturnSweep(t2);
3108  }
3109 /* if (!InterruptRun)

3860  sc2 = (P.Mean_TimeToTest > 0) ? exp(-P.Mean_TimeToTestOffset / P.Mean_TimeToTest) : 0.0;

3874  }

4015  double* SARI_a, * Critical_a, * CritRecov_a, * incSARI_a, * incCritical_a, * incCritRecov_a, sc1a, sc2a,sc3a,sc4a; //this stuff corrects bed prevalence for exponentially distributed time to test results in hospital
4016 
4017  if (!(SARI_a = (double*)malloc(MAX_ADUNITS * sizeof(double)))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to allocate temp storage\n");
4018  if (!(Critical_a = (double*)malloc(MAX_ADUNITS * sizeof(double)))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to allocate temp storage\n");

4023  sc1a = (P.Mean_TimeToTest > 0) ? exp(-1.0 / P.Mean_TimeToTest) : 0.0;
4024  sc2a = (P.Mean_TimeToTest > 0) ? exp(-P.Mean_TimeToTestOffset / P.Mean_TimeToTest) : 0.0;
4025  sc3a = (P.Mean_TimeToTest > 0) ? exp(-P.Mean_TimeToTestCriticalOffset / P.Mean_TimeToTest) : 0.0;
4026  sc4a = (P.Mean_TimeToTest > 0) ? exp(-P.Mean_TimeToTestCritRecovOffset / P.Mean_TimeToTest) : 0.0;

4183 void LoadSnapshot(void)
4184 {
4185  FILE* dat;
4186  int i, j, * CellMemberArray, * CellSuscMemberArray;
4187  long l;
4188  long long CM_offset, CSM_offset;
4189  double t;
4190  int** Array_InvCDF;
4191  float* Array_tot_prob, ** Array_cum_trans, ** Array_max_trans;
4192 
4193  if (!(dat = fopen(SnapshotLoadFile, "rb"))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to open snapshot file\n");
4194  fprintf(stderr, "Loading snapshot.");
4195  if (!(Array_InvCDF = (int**)malloc(P.NCP * sizeof(int*)))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to allocate temp cell storage\n");
4196  if (!(Array_max_trans = (float**)malloc(P.NCP * sizeof(float*)))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to temp allocate cell storage\n");
4197  if (!(Array_cum_trans = (float**)malloc(P.NCP * sizeof(float*)))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to temp allocate cell storage\n");
4198  if (!(Array_tot_prob = (float*)malloc(P.NCP * sizeof(float)))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to temp allocate cell storage\n");
4199  for (i = 0; i < P.NCP; i++)
4200  {
4201  Array_InvCDF[i] = Cells[i].InvCDF;
4202  Array_max_trans[i] = Cells[i].max_trans;
4203  Array_cum_trans[i] = Cells[i].cum_trans;
4204  Array_tot_prob[i] = Cells[i].tot_prob;
4205  }
4206 
4207  fread_big((void*)& i, sizeof(int), 1, dat); if (i != P.PopSize) ERR_CRITICAL_FMT("Incorrect N (%i %i) in snapshot file.\n", P.PopSize, i);
4208  fread_big((void*)& i, sizeof(int), 1, dat); if (i != P.NH) ERR_CRITICAL("Incorrect NH in snapshot file.\n");
4209  fread_big((void*)&i, sizeof(int), 1, dat); if (i != P.NC) ERR_CRITICAL_FMT("## %i neq %i\nIncorrect NC in snapshot file.", i, P.NC);
4210  fread_big((void*)& i, sizeof(int), 1, dat); if (i != P.NCP) ERR_CRITICAL("Incorrect NCP in snapshot file.\n");
4211  fread_big((void*)& i, sizeof(int), 1, dat); if (i != P.ncw) ERR_CRITICAL("Incorrect ncw in snapshot file.\n");
4212  fread_big((void*)& i, sizeof(int), 1, dat); if (i != P.nch) ERR_CRITICAL("Incorrect nch in snapshot file.\n");
4213  fread_big((void*)& l, sizeof(long), 1, dat); if (l != P.setupSeed1) ERR_CRITICAL("Incorrect setupSeed1 in snapshot file.\n");
4214  fread_big((void*)& l, sizeof(long), 1, dat); if (l != P.setupSeed2) ERR_CRITICAL("Incorrect setupSeed2 in snapshot file.\n");
4215  fread_big((void*)& t, sizeof(double), 1, dat); if (t != P.TimeStep) ERR_CRITICAL("Incorrect TimeStep in snapshot file.\n");
4216  fread_big((void*) & (P.SnapshotLoadTime), sizeof(double), 1, dat);
4217  P.NumSamples = 1 + (int)ceil((P.SampleTime - P.SnapshotLoadTime) / P.SampleStep);
4218  fprintf(stderr, ".");
4219  fread_big((void*)& CellMemberArray, sizeof(int*), 1, dat);
4220  fprintf(stderr, ".");
4221  fread_big((void*)& CellSuscMemberArray, sizeof(int*), 1, dat);
4222  fprintf(stderr, ".");
4223  CM_offset = State.CellMemberArray - CellMemberArray;
4224  CSM_offset = State.CellSuscMemberArray - CellSuscMemberArray;
4225 
4226  fread_big((void*)Hosts, sizeof(Person), (size_t)P.PopSize, dat);
4227  fprintf(stderr, ".");
4228  fread_big((void*)Households, sizeof(Household), (size_t)P.NH, dat);
4229  fprintf(stderr, ".");
4230  fread_big((void*)Cells, sizeof(Cell), (size_t)P.NC, dat);
4231  fprintf(stderr, ".");
4232  fread_big((void*)Mcells, sizeof(Microcell), (size_t)P.NMC, dat);
4233  fprintf(stderr, ".");
4234  fread_big((void*)State.CellMemberArray, sizeof(int), (size_t)P.PopSize, dat);
4235  fprintf(stderr, ".");
4236  fread_big((void*)State.CellSuscMemberArray, sizeof(int), (size_t)P.PopSize, dat);
4237  fprintf(stderr, ".");
4238  for (i = 0; i < P.NC; i++)
4239  {
4240  if (Cells[i].n > 0)
4241  {
4242  Cells[i].members += CM_offset;
4243  Cells[i].susceptible += CSM_offset;
4244  Cells[i].latent += CSM_offset;
4245  Cells[i].infected += CSM_offset;
4246  }
4247  for (j = 0; j < MAX_INTERVENTION_TYPES; j++) Cells[i].CurInterv[j] = -1; // turn interventions off in loaded image
4248  }
4249  for (i = 0; i < P.NMC; i++)
4250  if (Mcells[i].n > 0)
4251  Mcells[i].members += CM_offset;
4252 
4253  for (i = 0; i < P.NCP; i++)
4254  {
4255  Cells[i].InvCDF = Array_InvCDF[i];
4256  Cells[i].max_trans = Array_max_trans[i];
4257  Cells[i].cum_trans = Array_cum_trans[i];
4258  Cells[i].tot_prob = Array_tot_prob[i];
4259  }
4260  free(Array_tot_prob);
4261  free(Array_cum_trans);
4262  free(Array_max_trans);
4263  free(Array_InvCDF);
4264  fprintf(stderr, "\n");
4265  fclose(dat);
4266 }

4268 void SaveSnapshot(void)
4269 {
4270  FILE* dat;
4271  int i = 1;
4272 
4273  if (!(dat = fopen(SnapshotSaveFile, "wb"))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to open snapshot file\n");
4274 
4275  fwrite_big((void*) & (P.PopSize), sizeof(int), 1, dat);

4278  fprintf(stderr, "## %i\n", i++);

4280  fprintf(stderr, "## %i\n", i++);
4281  fwrite_big((void*) & (P.NCP), sizeof(int), 1, dat);

4317 
4318 void UpdateProbs(int DoPlace)
4319 {
4320  if (!DoPlace)
4321  {
4322 #pragma omp parallel for schedule(static,500) default(none) \
4323  shared(P, CellLookup)
4324  for (int j = 0; j < P.NCP; j++)
4325  {
4326  CellLookup[j]->tot_prob = 0;
4327  CellLookup[j]->S0 = CellLookup[j]->S + CellLookup[j]->L + CellLookup[j]->I;
4328  if (P.DoDeath)
4329  {
4330  CellLookup[j]->S0 += CellLookup[j]->n / 5;
4331  if ((CellLookup[j]->n < 100) || (CellLookup[j]->S0 > CellLookup[j]->n)) CellLookup[j]->S0 = CellLookup[j]->n;
4332  }
4333  }
4334  }
4335  else
4336  {
4337 #pragma omp parallel for schedule(static,500) default(none) \
4338  shared(P, CellLookup)
4339  for (int j = 0; j < P.NCP; j++)
4340  {
4341  CellLookup[j]->S0 = CellLookup[j]->S;
4342  CellLookup[j]->tot_prob = 0;
4343  }
4344  }
4345 #pragma omp parallel for schedule(static,500) default(none) \
4346  shared(P, CellLookup)
4347  for (int j = 0; j < P.NCP; j++)
4348  {
4349  int m, k;
4350  float t;
4351  CellLookup[j]->cum_trans[0] = ((float)(CellLookup[0]->S0)) * CellLookup[j]->max_trans[0];
4352  t = ((float)CellLookup[0]->n) * CellLookup[j]->max_trans[0];
4353  for (m = 1; m < P.NCP; m++)
4354  {
4355  CellLookup[j]->cum_trans[m] = CellLookup[j]->cum_trans[m - 1] + ((float)(CellLookup[m]->S0)) * CellLookup[j]->max_trans[m];
4356  t += ((float)CellLookup[m]->n) * CellLookup[j]->max_trans[m];
4357  }
4358  CellLookup[j]->tot_prob = CellLookup[j]->cum_trans[P.NCP - 1];
4359  for (m = 0; m < P.NCP; m++)
4360  CellLookup[j]->cum_trans[m] /= CellLookup[j]->tot_prob;
4361  CellLookup[j]->tot_prob /= t;
4362  for (k = m = 0; k <= 1024; k++)
4363  {
4364  while (CellLookup[j]->cum_trans[m] * 1024 < ((float)k)) m++;
4365  CellLookup[j]->InvCDF[k] = m;
4366  }
4367  }
4368 }

4370 int ChooseTriggerVariableAndValue(int AdUnit)
4371 {
4372  int VariableAndValue = 0;
4373  if (P.DoGlobalTriggers)
4374  {
4375  if (P.DoPerCapitaTriggers)
4376  VariableAndValue = (int)floor(((double)State.trigDC) * P.GlobalIncThreshPop / ((double)P.PopSize));
4377  else
4378  VariableAndValue = State.trigDC;
4379  }
4380  else if (P.DoAdminTriggers) VariableAndValue = State.trigDC_adunit[AdUnit];
4381  else VariableAndValue = INT_MAX;
4382 
4383  return VariableAndValue;
4384 }
4385 double ChooseThreshold(int AdUnit, double WhichThreshold)
4386 {
4387  double Threshold = 0;
4388  if (P.DoGlobalTriggers) Threshold = WhichThreshold;
4389  else if (P.DoAdminTriggers)
4390  {
4391  if (P.DoPerCapitaTriggers)
4392  Threshold = (int)ceil(((double)(AdUnits[AdUnit].n * WhichThreshold)) / P.IncThreshPop);
4393  else
4394  Threshold = WhichThreshold;
4395  }
4396  return Threshold;
4397 }

5125  P.EnhancedSocDistSpatialEffectCurrent = P.EnhancedSocDistSpatialEffect2;
5126  for (int i = 0; i < P.PlaceTypeNum; i++)
5127  {
5128  P.SocDistPlaceEffectCurrent[i] = P.SocDistPlaceEffect2[i];
5129  P.EnhancedSocDistPlaceEffectCurrent[i] = P.EnhancedSocDistPlaceEffect2[i];
5130  }
5131  }
5132  //fix to switch off first place closure after P.PlaceCloseDuration has elapsed, if there are no school or cell-based triggers set
5133  if (t == P.PlaceCloseTimeStart + P.PlaceCloseDuration)
5134  {
5135  P.PlaceCloseTimeStartPrevious = P.PlaceCloseTimeStart;
5136  if ((P.PlaceCloseIncTrig == 0) && (P.PlaceCloseFracIncTrig == 0) && (P.PlaceCloseCellIncThresh == 0)) P.PlaceCloseTimeStart = 9e9;
5137  }
5138 
5139  if (!P.VaryEfficaciesOverTime)
5140  {
5141  if ((P.PlaceCloseTimeStart2 > P.PlaceCloseTimeStartPrevious) &&
5142  (t >= P.PlaceCloseTimeStartPrevious + P.PlaceCloseDuration) &&
5143  (t >= P.PlaceCloseTimeStartPrevious + P.PlaceCloseTimeStartBase2 - P.PlaceCloseTimeStartBase))
5144  {
5145  fprintf(stderr, "\nSecond place closure period (t=%lg)\n", t);
5146  P.PlaceCloseTimeStartPrevious = P.PlaceCloseTimeStart2 = P.PlaceCloseTimeStart = t;
5147  P.PlaceCloseDuration = P.PlaceCloseDuration2;
5148  P.PlaceCloseIncTrig = P.PlaceCloseIncTrig2;
5149  P.PlaceCloseCellIncThresh = P.PlaceCloseCellIncThresh2;
5150  }
5151  }
5152 
5153  if (P.OutputBitmap >= 1)
5154  {
5155  TSMean = TSMeanNE; TSVar = TSVarNE;
5156  CaptureBitmap ();
5157  OutputBitmap (0);
5158  }
5159 }

5221  TimeSeries[(int)(Hosts[i2].latent_time * P.TimeStep / P.SampleStep)].Rage[HOST_AGE_GROUP(i)]++;
5222  }
5223  }
5224  }
5225  inftype[Hosts[i].infect_type % INFECT_TYPE_MASK]++;
5226  j--;

5228  {
5229  if (l < 0) l = 0;
5230  inf_household[k][l]++;
5231  case_household[k][lc2]++; //now recording total symptomatic cases, rather than infections conditional on symptomatic index
5232  l = lc = lc2 = 0; t = 1e10;
5233  }
5234  }
5235  }
5236  for (b = 0; b < P.NC; b++)
5237  if ((Cells[b].S != Cells[b].n) || (Cells[b].R > 0))

5239  {

5245  }
5246  }

5250  for (i = 0; i < MAX_COUNTRIES; i++)

5253  if (infcountry[i] > 0) infcountry_num[i]++;
5254  }
5255  for (i = 0; i < MAX_SEC_REC; i++)
5256  for (j = 0; j < MAX_GEN_REC; j++)
5257  indivR0_av[i][j] += indivR0[i][j];
5258  for (i = 0; i <= MAX_HOUSEHOLD_SIZE; i++)
5259  for (j = 0; j <= MAX_HOUSEHOLD_SIZE; j++)
5260  {
5261  inf_household_av[i][j] += inf_household[i][j];
5262  case_household_av[i][j] += case_household[i][j];
5263  }
5264  }

5266  for (n = 0; n < P.NumSamples; n++)
5267  {
5268  TimeSeries[n].t += k;
5269  s = 0;

5271  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++)
5272  TimeSeries[n].Rage[i] /= TimeSeries[n].Rdenom;
5273  for (i = 0; i < INFECT_TYPE_MASK; i++)
5274  s += (TimeSeries[n].Rtype[i] /= TimeSeries[n].Rdenom);
5275  TimeSeries[n].Rdenom = s;
5276  }
5277  nf = sizeof(Results) / sizeof(double);
5278  if (!P.DoAdUnits) nf -= MAX_ADUNITS; // TODO: This still processes most of the AdUnit arrays; just not the last one
5279  fprintf(stderr, "extinct=%i (%i)\n", (int) TimeSeries[P.NumSamples - 1].extinct, P.NumSamples - 1);
5280  if (TimeSeries[P.NumSamples - 1].extinct)
5281  {
5282  TSMean = TSMeanE; TSVar = TSVarE; P.NRactE++;
5283  }
5284  else
5285  {
5286  TSMean = TSMeanNE; TSVar = TSVarNE; P.NRactNE++;
5287  }
5288  lc = -k;
5289  for (n = 0; n < P.NumSamples; n++)
5290  {
5291  if ((n + lc >= 0) && (n + lc < P.NumSamples))
5292  {
5293  if (s < TimeSeries[n + lc].incC) { s = TimeSeries[n + lc].incC; t = P.SampleStep * ((double)(n + lc)); }
5294  res = (double*)&TimeSeries[n + lc];
5295  res_av = (double*)&TSMean[n];
5296  res_var = (double*)&TSVar[n];
5297  for (i = 1 /* skip over `t` */; i < nf; i++)
5298  {
5299  res_av[i] += res[i];
5300  res_var[i] += res[i] * res[i];
5301  }
5302  if (TSMean[n].cumTmax < TimeSeries[n + lc].cumT) TSMean[n].cumTmax = TimeSeries[n + lc].cumT;
5303  if (TSMean[n].cumVmax < TimeSeries[n + lc].cumV) TSMean[n].cumVmax = TimeSeries[n + lc].cumV;
5304  }
5305  TSMean[n].t += ((double) n )* P.SampleStep;
5306  }
5307  PeakHeightSum += s;
5308  PeakHeightSS += s * s;
5309  PeakTimeSum += t;
5310  PeakTimeSS += t * t;
5311 }

5314 void CalcOriginDestMatrix_adunit()
5315 {
5327 #pragma omp parallel for schedule(static) default(none) \
5328  shared(P, Cells, CellLookup, Mcells, StateT)
5329  for (int tn = 0; tn < P.NumThreads; tn++)
5330  {
5331  for (int i = tn; i < P.NCP; i += P.NumThreads)
5332  {
5333  //reset pop density matrix to zero
5334  double pop_dens_from[MAX_ADUNITS] = {};
5335 
5336  //find index of cell from which flow travels
5337  ptrdiff_t cl_from = CellLookup[i] - Cells;
5338  ptrdiff_t cl_from_mcl = (cl_from / P.nch) * P.NMCL * P.nmch + (cl_from % P.nch) * P.NMCL;
5339 
5340  //loop over microcells in these cells to find populations in each admin unit and so flows
5341  for (int k = 0; k < P.NMCL; k++)
5342  {
5343  for (int l = 0; l < P.NMCL; l++)
5344  {
5345  //get index of microcell
5346  ptrdiff_t mcl_from = cl_from_mcl + l + k * P.nmch;
5347  if (Mcells[mcl_from].n > 0)
5348  {
5349  //get proportion of each population of cell that exists in each admin unit
5350  pop_dens_from[Mcells[mcl_from].adunit] += (((double)Mcells[mcl_from].n) / ((double)Cells[cl_from].n));
5351  }
5352  }
5353  }
5354 
5355  for (int j = i; j < P.NCP; j++)
5356  {
5357  //reset pop density matrix to zero
5358  double pop_dens_to[MAX_ADUNITS] = {};
5359 
5360  //find index of cell which flow travels to
5361  ptrdiff_t cl_to = CellLookup[j] - Cells;
5362  ptrdiff_t cl_to_mcl = (cl_to / P.nch) * P.NMCL * P.nmch + (cl_to % P.nch) * P.NMCL;
5363  //calculate distance and kernel between the cells
5364  //total_flow=Cells[cl_from].max_trans[j]*Cells[cl_from].n*Cells[cl_to].n;
5365  double total_flow;
5366  if (j == 0)
5367  {
5368  total_flow = Cells[cl_from].cum_trans[j] * Cells[cl_from].n;
5369  }
5370  else
5371  {
5372  total_flow = (Cells[cl_from].cum_trans[j] - Cells[cl_from].cum_trans[j - 1]) * Cells[cl_from].n;
5373  }
5374 
5375  //loop over microcells within destination cell
5376  for (int m = 0; m < P.NMCL; m++)
5377  {
5378  for (int p = 0; p < P.NMCL; p++)
5379  {
5380  //get index of microcell
5381  ptrdiff_t mcl_to = cl_to_mcl + p + m * P.nmch;
5382  if (Mcells[mcl_to].n > 0)
5383  {
5384  //get proportion of each population of cell that exists in each admin unit
5385  pop_dens_to[Mcells[mcl_to].adunit] += (((double)Mcells[mcl_to].n) / ((double)Cells[cl_to].n));
5386  }
5387  }
5388  }
5389 
5390  for (int m = 0; m < P.NumAdunits; m++)
5391  {
5392  for (int p = 0; p < P.NumAdunits; p++)
5393  {
5394  if (m != p)
5395  {
5396  double flow = total_flow * pop_dens_from[m] * pop_dens_to[p]; //updated to remove reference to cross-border flows: ggilani 26/03/20
5397  StateT[tn].origin_dest[m][p] += flow;
5398  StateT[tn].origin_dest[p][m] += flow;
5399  }
5400  }
5401  }
5402  }
5403 
5405  //k=(cl_from/P.nch)*P.NMCL*P.nmch+(cl_from%P.nch)*P.NMCL;
5406  //for(l=0;l<P.NMCL;l++)
5407  //{
5408  // for(m=0;m<P.NMCL;m++)
5409  // {
5410  // mcl_from=k+m+l*P.nmch;
5411  // pop_cell_from[Mcells[mcl_from].adunit]+=Mcells[mcl_from].n;
5412  // }
5413  //}
5415  //for(p=(i+1);p<P.NCP;p++)
5416  //{
5417  // //reset population array
5418  // for(j=0;j<P.NumAdunits;j++)
5419  // {
5420  // pop_cell_to[j]=0.0;
5421  // }
5422  // cl_to=CellLookup[p]-Cells;
5423  // //loop over microcells within cell to find the proportion of the cell population in each admin unit
5424  // q=(cl_to/P.nch)*P.NMCL*P.nmch+(cl_to%P.nch)*P.NMCL;
5425  // for(l=0;l<P.NMCL;l++)
5426  // {
5427  // for(m=0;m<P.NMCL;m++)
5428  // {
5429  // mcl_to=q+m+l*P.nmch;
5430  // pop_cell_to[Mcells[mcl_to].adunit]+=Mcells[mcl_to].n;
5431  // }
5432  // }
5433 
5434  // //find distance and kernel function between cells
5435  // dist=dist2_cc_min(Cells+cl_from,Cells+cl_to);
5436  // dist_kernel=numKernel(dist);
5437

5439  // for(l=0;l<P.NumAdunits;l++)
5440  // {
5441  // for(m=(l+1);m<P.NumAdunits;m++)

5445  // }
5446  // }

5455  {
5456  for (int k = 0; k < P.NumThreads; k++)
5457  {
5458  AdUnits[i].origin_dest[j] += StateT[k].origin_dest[i][j];
5459  }
5460  }
5461  }

5486 /*
5487  Reads a string (as per fscanf %s).
5488  Returns true if it succeeds, false on EOF, and does not return on error.
5489 */
5490 bool readString(const char* SItemName, FILE* dat, char *buf) {
5491  int r = fscanf(dat, "%s", buf);
5492  if(r == 1) {
5493  return true;
5494  } else if (r == EOF) {
5495  if(ferror(dat)) {
5496  ERR_CRITICAL_FMT("fscanf failed for %s: %s.\n", SItemName, strerror(errno));
5497  } else {
5498  // EOF
5499  return false;
5500  }
5501  } else {
5502  ERR_CRITICAL_FMT("Unexpected fscanf result %d for %s.\n", r, SItemName);
5503  }
5504 }

5506 int GetInputParameter3(FILE* dat, const char* SItemName, const char* ItemType, void* ItemPtr, int NumItem, int NumItem2, int Offset)
5507 {

5509  int FindFlag = 0, EndString, CurPos, i, j, n;
5510

5513  sprintf(ItemName, "[%s]", SItemName);
5514  while (!FindFlag)
5515  {

5517  FindFlag = (!strncmp(match, ItemName, strlen(match)));
5518  if (FindFlag)
5519  {

5523  while ((!EndString) && (FindFlag))

5527  strcat(ReadItemName, match);

5530  }

5532  {
5533  fseek(dat, CurPos, 0);
5534  FindFlag = 0;
5535  }
5536  }
5537  }
5538  if (FindFlag)
5539  {
5540  FindFlag = 0;
5541  if (!strcmp(ItemType, "%lf")) n = 1;

5543  else if (!strcmp(ItemType, "%s")) n = 3;

5644  for (i = 0; i < NumItem2; i++)
5645  {
5646  if(fscanf(dat, "%s", match) != 1) { ERR_CRITICAL_FMT("fscanf failed for %s\n", SItemName); }
5647  if ((match[0] != '[') && (!feof(dat)))
5648  {
5649  FindFlag++;
5650  if (n == 1)
5651  sscanf(match, "%lf", ((double**)ItemPtr)[j + Offset] + i + Offset); //changed from [j+Offset]+i+Offset to +j+Offset+i, as ItemPtr isn't an array - 01/10: changed it back
5652  else
5653  sscanf(match, "%i", ((int**)ItemPtr)[j + Offset] + i + Offset);
5654  }
5655  else
5656  {
5657  i = NumItem2;
5658  j = NumItem;
5659  }
5660  }
5661  //Offset=Offset+(NumItem2-1); //added this line to get the correct offset in address position when incrementing j
5662  } //added these braces
5663  }
5664  }
5665  // fprintf(stderr,"%s\n",SItemName);
5666  return FindFlag;
5667 }
